The article describes{{clarify|date=October 2016}} the state of '''[[race relations]] and [[racism]] in a number of countries'''.

Various forms of racism are practiced in most countries on Earth.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://web.amnesty.org/library/index/engACT400202001 |publisher=Amnesty International |title=Racism and the administration of justice |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041227005600/http://web.amnesty.org/library/index/engACT400202001 |archivedate=December 27, 2004 }}</ref> In individual countries, the forms of racism which are practiced may be motivated by historic, cultural, religious, economic or demographic reasons. Wars created sentiments of ultra-nationalism, ethnic pride and racism.

Racism is widely condemned throughout the world, with 88 states being signatories of the [[International Convention on the Elimination of All Forms of Racial Discrimination]] {{as of|2013|3|7|lc=on}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://treaties.un.org/Pages/ViewDetails.aspx?src=TREATY&mtdsg_no=IV-2&chapter=4&lang=en|title=STATUS AS AT : 07-03-2013 05:04:14 EDT : International Convention on the Elimination of All Forms of Racial Discrimination|publisher=[[Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights]]}}</ref>
* [[Racism in Asia]]
After the [[Opium Wars]] in [[China]], a nationalist feeling which was linked with race surged in popularity and it was motivated by the desire to fight against foreign influence and control, along with the desire to ensure that the majority of the population of China would only be of Chinese origin.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Pfafman|first=Tessa M.|last2=Carpenter|first2=Christopher J.|last3=Tang|first3=Yong|date=December 2015|title=The Politics of Racism: Constructions of African Immigrants in China on ChinaSMACK: Racism on ChinaSMACK|url=https://academic.oup.com/ccc/article/8/4/540-556/3979293|journal=Communication, Culture & Critique|language=en|volume=8|issue=4|pages=540â€“556|doi=10.1111/cccr.12098}}</ref>

